      "notes": [
        "Bytes 2/3/7 are profile bytes and are not globally fixed across all gun templates.",
        "AA/HH in standard templates correlate with ammo/health capacity classes (for example 0x0a vs 0x0d/0x0f and 0x12 profile family in Test 10).",
        "DD behaves like a damage profile selector; live per-hit damage is carried by 5a3f01TT0000 and echoed in 30013fTTNN.",
        "Do not treat AA/DD/HH as universally direct runtime counters; semantics depend on template family.",
        "Byte deltas beyond LL vary across progression/upgrades.",
        "In standard form C (36 00 0d 03 02 03 00 0f LL NN MM 00 VV): VV=03 when reactivation-time is selected and reload-speed is not selected (Test 7), VV=04 when reload-speed is selected and reactivation-time is not selected (Test 6).",
        "Seen trailing variants include 04, 03, and 0a in different phases.",
        "Alternate gun profile (Test 10) uses bytes 2-6: 12 01 02 00 01 or 12 01 03 03 01 or 12 02 03 03 01."
